BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pssVPso_McCZnDZZCCw_m
SUMMARY:LANDSCAPE TECHNICIAN BOOTCAMP
DTSTAMP:20260401T023629Z
DTSTART:20260403T140000Z
DESCRIPTION:LANDSCAPE TECHNICIAN BOOTCAMP Friday\, April 3\, 2026 Lake Wash
	ington Institute of Technology – 11605 132nd Avenue NE\, Kirkland\, WA 980
	34-8506 TITLE SPONSOR - DURANTA The Washington Association of Landscape Pr
	ofessionals is excited to offer the LANDSCAPE TECHNICIAN BOOTCAMP training
	 in partnership with the National Association of Landscape Professionals. 
	WALP will be offering the LANDSCAPE TECHNICIAN BOOTCAMP in APRIL 3\, 2026 
	at Lake Washington Insitute of Technology that will be comprehensive train
	ing for your staff and workforce. Hands-On Training For Your Crews! The ne
	w Landscape Technician Boot Camp will provide hands-on training for your c
	rews. Based on the curriculum for the Landscape Industry Certified Technic
	ian Exterior exam\, this industry-vetted training will help prepare your c
	rews to work more effectively in 2026.  Boot Camp includes training in tec
	hniques and safety in 15 different competency areas organized into 3 disci
	plines presented in Spanish and English! Bonus! This course also helps pre
	pare people for the Landscape Industry Certified Technician Exterior exam.
	 So\, once you’ve trained your team\, consider registering them to become 
	certified through the National Association of Landscape Professionals \\(N
	ALP\\). Registration Costs: WALP Members \\(First 5 registrants\\): $95.00
	 per person WALP Members \\(6\\+ registrants\\): $80.00 per person NON-WAL
	P Members : $145.00 per person\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/de
	tails/landscape-technician-bootcamp/18291064/2026-04-03T00\n\nFrom SEAtoda
